Map=(MapName="DH-Brecourt_Push",Acronym=DH,PlayerCountMin=6,PlayerCountMax=32,FriendlyName=DH-Brecourt_Push.LevelSummary.Title,Author="Darkest Hour Team",ScreenShot=DH-Brecourt_Push.PreviewSS.Preview,Description=DH-Brecourt_Push.LevelSummary.Description,FallbackDesc="June 6th 1944||By the Summer of 1944 the Allies of the West were finally ready to answer Stalin's pleas and demands that a front be opened against the Third Reich in Western Europe.||This would be called Operation Overlord.||Success in France could reduce German strength on the Eastern Front to the point where Stalin's massive armies could begin to make speedy, unstoppable progress toward the taking of Berlin. It would also complete the encirclement of the Reich with attacking armies in the East, West, Italy in the South in addition to the loss of the German Ally, Finland, in the North.||This is one of the initial battles of Operation Overlord, the Allied Invasion of Fortress Europe. The first full-sized combat formations to enter the battle were parachute and glider-borne troops. They were tasked with taking or destroying critical positons like bridges, artillery positions, communication and transportation nodes.||With luck they would face second-rate German units, lightly equipped and soft from years of occupation duty. But, first rate formations were present and rushed into battle with skilled and hardened veterans and superb leaders.||When clashes ocurred between these elite formation of both sides, neither of whom would give an inch, the results were bloody and decisive.",FallbackName="Brecourt")